Nigeria in Job Security Talks for Power Industry, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-17T08:08:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/nigeria-in-job-security-talks-for-power-industry-thisday-says.html
Nigeria ’s government is in talks with
labor unions about  job security  in the power industry once
state-owned companies are sold,  ThisDay reported , citing Hassan
Sunmonu, a government-appointed negotiator.  Nigeria,  Africa ’s most populous nation and top oil
producer, plans to sell six state-owned transmission and 11
thermal-generation companies by July, according to the power
ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburgt . 